parameters:
--Stamina and skill power have been \c[24]fully
restored\c[0]!

--! It's okay, Momiji-san!? Sorry I'm late! Are you
injured...!?
I'm fine... Most of my wounds have already closed up.
That's good. It seems there's no danger to your life.
You've come, Karin--and alone at that?

I've kept you waiting, Koutarou... On my way here, I learned
about various things that happened in the past in this Fuma
village.

Ho... That's a different tone than before. Your mother,
Yobirin-dono, had mysterious powers as a Miko,
indeed. So it seems that power has certainly been passed
down to you, her daughter.

Yes... With that mysterious power, I was able to understand
the past. Momiji-san, thank you for taking care of me so
much when I was a baby. I found out why my father, mother,
and I were able to live so long. We had turned into stone.

Yes. My mother used a spell to turn the three of us to
stone. It seems we spent over a hundred years in the pond.
Honestly, I was surprised too...

...When Chuutaro escaped from prison and we caught up to
him, we saw the three of you jump into the pond but never
resurface. We thought you had died, but no one there could
have imagined that you had turned to stone and survived.

To turn living humans into stone... I can't believe Yorin-
san could do such a thing...

I once heard from Gyouon. Among the demon-slaying shrine
maidens, there were those who possessed techniques beyond
human knowledge, including those who could petrify demons
and seal them away--I see, so Yorin-dono was a descendant
of those shrine maidens.

...It seems so. But my mother died using the petrification
technique... She sacrificed her own life to save me and my
father...

If what you say about seeing Fuma village's past is true,
then all the more reason you cannot forgive me? Indirectly,
I have killed your mother... Is that not so, Karin--?

Being forced to imprison my father against my will and
getting caught up in the war and reluctantly eating demon
flesh to become a demon... I sympathize with what happened
in Fuma village in the past... but...

That doesn't mean I can allow evil deeds. As a surviving
member of the Fuma clan, I must defeat you who have fallen
both body and soul to demonhood, in place of my father,
Chuutaro--!

Hmph. You're a daughter with a strong sense of justice, just
like Chuutaro. Did you come here alone because you wanted a
one-on-one fight? Good spirit. No tricks then. Let's fight
head-on.

Momiji-san, you don't need to help. It must be hard for you
to fight against your own father, right? I will defeat
Koutarou here, the last head of Fuma.

Very well. There are only three of us Fuma left now. Let
these fists explain which of us is right. Come on! Prepare
yourself, Chuutaro's daughter, Karin--!
Fine by me! I'll show you my true strength!
--Fuma Demon Koutarou has initiated the battle!
Guhh!? No, not yet... I can still fight!
This is the final blow! Yaaaaaaaah!!

--Fuma Demon Koutarou has coughed up blood and fallen to the
ground!

To defeat Father alone like that... amazing... Karin-chan,
are you injured...!?

Hah... hah... I'm okay. It seems the fight with Koutarou has
finally been settled.
Guhhh--! No, not yet...! It's not over yet...!

In the world of ninja, a conclusion means taking the life
of your opponent. As long as my heart is beating, the match
isn't over yet, Karin!

Fuu, haa...! What's wrong? Hurry up and finish me. Are you
saying you want to shame me, the last head of the Fuma clan,
by letting me live in disgrace? If you let time pass, my
wounds will fully heal.

...You are my uncle, my father's brother, and Momiji-san's
father. You are undoubtedly one of my blood relatives. The
fight is already over. This is my conclusion--

--Gahhahhah! How soft! Such mercy and pity towards an enemy
would not have allowed one to survive in the Warring States
period, it's a contemptible way of thinking!

That may be true. But this is not the age of bloodshed and
war anymore.

All these graves in the village, you built them, didn't you?
To mourn and pray for the souls of the villagers who died in
the wars...

The peaceful world that those men and women who died wished
for. A world where weapons are put away for a hundred years
--and even further, an era where all living creatures are
treated with compassion.

Hmph... So the Fuma village has been destroyed for 123 years
--I've lived too long, to the point where there's no place
for us anymore... is that it?

Momiji. You must survive along with Karin. If there is no
gravekeeper, the tombstones of those from Fuma here will
fall into ruin...
...Eh!? What are you planning to do--!?

The Fuma bloodline must not be extinguished... My daughter,
Momiji--my niece, Karin--do not forget the pride of our
clan...

...It's the last trap I prepared. Now both of you, hurry
outside. If you stay here, you'll be crushed under the heavy
tiled roof.

...Momiji... I'm sorry for everything up until now...
Forgive your foolish father who continued to choose the
wrong path.

Both of you survive! This is my last technique--! Retsuha
Senpuuzan--!!
--Karin and Momiji were blown outside of the mansion!

Henceforth, we declare Kotaro-dono as our new leader of the
Fuma clan--!

Haha-! The people of Fuma village will work diligently for
our lord Kotaro-sama!

Now then, Kotaro-sama. Please accept the Fuma clan's
guardian sword, the symbol of our headship.
Really... Am I truly fit to be the new head?

We have discussed this many times and decided. There are no
objections. Kotaro-dono is indeed worthy to lead the Fuma.

To think that Kotaro, whom I've guided since he was young,
would become our new leader, it moves me deeply... Hohoho!

...Tch! I think Kotaro-san would be more suitable as the
leader though...

Hey! You shouldn't speak like that, Aomaru! My apologies,
Kotaro-sama!

Wouldn't Fuma develop further if a well-known elder brother
took over?

I've become too famous. If I were to succeed the Fuma, it
would anger both Kai and Echigo, becoming a source of
disaster. I can trust you to lead.
Guide the reborn Fuma, Kotaro--no, our lord--
We shall serve with utmost loyalty!

Indeed! I, Kotaro, will take on all responsibilities and
succeed the name of the Fuma clan head! Please, everyone,
follow me! I'm counting on you!
Oh--! Long live the Fuma clan!

Heh... I've even lost the guardian sword of Fuma, the symbol
of the headship. The end of a long dream... this memorable
Fuma mansion... huh...

...I'm sorry, Momiji-san. It's because I defeated Uncle
Kotaro...

No. I'm sure father accepted his end and activated the trap
himself.

Ever since becoming a demon, he must have been seeking his
own place of death...
Hey! Are you two alright, any injuries?
I was worried because you were late, so I came to meet you!

Oh! You're alive, Momiji! Even with a demon's regenerative
abilities, I was worried!
I'm sorry, Master. My injuries have already fully healed.
What about him? What happened to Kotaro?
After saving us, he was buried under this mansion.

...Yes. Perhaps father thought that the village where he was
born and raised was fitting to be his final resting place.

Hmm... The Fuma mansion as Kotaro's gravestone... How
sorrowful...
I am Shikigumo--a direct subordinate of Lord Gyon.

That form, are you some kind of shikigami!? What business do
you have showing up here alone!

Well done on subduing Fuma--while you were busy, we've taken
Edo--I was told to convey that message.
--Look to the eastern sky! Fire and smoke...!
